        "text": "<p data-aid=\"141537350\" id=\"note26_p1\">Generations can learn from each other, even as each generation learns for itself. The Christian writer S&#xF8;ren Kierkegaard intriguingly suggests, &#x201C;Whatever the one generation may learn from the other, the genuinely humane no generation learns from the foregoing&#x201D; (<cite>Fear and Trembling,<\/cite> trans. Vigilius Haufniensi [2018], 117).<\/p>"
      },
